"adj. 各式各样，各种的 【英】 adj. 各式各样，各种的 (miscellaneous, various) 【记】 分割记忆：sun(太阳) ＋dry(干)，太阳晒干 各种东西 【例】 a sundry revenue(杂项税收) adj. 各式各样的 = miscellaneous 【记】sun太阳, dry干－太阳晒干各种东西 【记】源自sunder 分裂，分裂成各式各样的东西；音：散缀，散布点缀的；sun + dry 干旱的太阳下，是有着各式各样东西的大千世界；Sunday 一到星期天，各式各样的人，东西全出来了 sundry (adj.)  Old English syndrig ""separate, apart, special, various, distinct, characteristic,"" from sundor ""separately, apart, asunder"" (see sunder) + -y (2). Compare Old High German suntaric, Swedish söndrig ""broken, tattered."" Meaning ""several"" is from 1375. As a noun, from mid-13c. with the sense ""various ones."" Phrase all and sundry is from late 14c."
